Review of Insignia Microwave

Insignia .7 CU is compact version for simple tasks as wattage is 700watts. It has numbered functions consisting of:
1. Time Cook;
2. Time Defrost;
3. Weight Defrost;
4. Power;
5. Clock;
6. Kitchen Timer;
7. Popcorn;
8. Potato;
9. Pizza;
10. Frozen Vegetables;
11. Beverage;
12. Dinner Plage
From the list, 7 to 12 are automate, and then it combine with number buttons 1 to 6.

Its power levels are 11 level, from 0 to 10, by 10% each level.

Out of package, it only includes turntable glass plate and carousel ring. Its product depth is 12 7/16 inches, width 17 13/16 inches, hight of 10 5/16 inches. Basically to picture it, measured against a bottle of wine, it reach about the neck of the bottle. 

As unique and handy functionality to mention:
1. I can set a memorized or saved function for most frequently used  option. 
2. Start button has included function to add 30 seconds to the already cooking time if needed.

Considering the size, it is quite functional for quick and simple need and still adjustable or almost depending one what being heat up. For instance, for popcorn, although it can immediately start with button Popcorn, it has option to adjust its weight. 

The only aspect that comes with it, it is if I have a bit larger size, have to divide and perform twice, or in the case of popcorn can’t place bags larger than 3.0 ounces.

The limitation mentioned is more due to the nature of the size and its capabilities, but other than that I find it very useful and doesn’t take much of space.

